  <!-- Description / Abstract -->
  <descriptions>
    <description xml:lang="en" descriptionType="Abstract">
      This dataset contains approximately 132,000 rows of telemetry data collected
      from three IoT environmental sensor devices. Each device records the following
      measurements: timestamp (Unix epoch), temperature (in degrees Celsius),
      humidity (as a percentage), light intensity (boolean), motion detection
      (boolean), and carbon monoxide (CO) levels. The data was collected in an
      indoor smart home environment and can be used for time-series analysis,
      anomaly detection, and machine learning classification tasks such as
      motion prediction using logistic regression.
    </description>
    <description xml:lang="en" descriptionType="Methods">
      Data was collected using three Raspberry Pi-based IoT sensor nodes
      identified by their MAC addresses. Sensors recorded environmental
      readings at regular intervals. Timestamps are stored as Unix epoch
      seconds and converted to human-readable datetime format for analysis.
      Outliers in temperature and humidity were removed using 1st and 99th
      percentile thresholds per device.
    </description>
  </descriptions>

